texts.text: v0.1.2 alpha was the first version released for iOS devices.[2] At this point, iOS devices had exclusive controls.

1 Changes
2 Internal Version
3 J-version
4 J-version demo
5 Demo
6 Gallery
7 References

Third person view "Back Only" for all devices.
Mirrored controls for left-handed players.
In-game sound toggle.
The license verification failure screen additionally contains the text "You need to be connected to the internet once while you start the game."
The internal version of v0.1.2 alpha is 0.1.2(1025) and has a size of 1.57 MB.
v0.1.2j alpha was released on Google Play on an unknown release date. The internal version is 0.1.2(1023) and has a size of 1.98 MB.

The title screen of the j version demo
A free J-version "lite" demo of v0.1.2 alpha was released on Google Play on an unknown release date.[citation needed] In mid-2014, it was removed from the Play/App stores. The internal version is the same as the j-version.

A free "lite" demo of v0.1.2 alpha was released on Google Play on an unknown release date.[3] In mid-2014, it was removed from the Play store. The internal version is not currently known.
A free "lite" demo of v0.1.2 alpha was also released on the iOS App Store on November 21, 2011. In mid-2014, it was removed from the App store.[4]
